definitions.definition: Any of several wormlike marine molluscs (not true worms ) of the family Teredinidae that bore through the wooden hulls of ships and other woody material immersed in salt water ; specifically, the naval shipworm or turu ( Teredo navalis ), the type species of the genus Teredo .
